    "department": "Corporate",
    "description": "LIFE AT UIPATH\n\nThe people at UiPath believe in the transformative power of automation to change how the world works. We’re committed to creating category-leading enterprise software that unleashes that power.\n\nTo make that happen, we need people who are curious, self-propelled, generous, and genuine. People who love being part of a fast-moving, fast-thinking growth company. And people who care—about each other, about UiPath, and about our larger purpose.\n\nCould that be you?\n\nYour mission\n\nThe UiPath Supply Chain and Retail team (Peak) is looking for a Delivery Manager to lead the successful implementation of AI solutions for our customers. You will ensure projects are delivered on time, within agreed scope and resource profile, and that customers see value as quickly as possible.\n\nThis exciting role sits at the intersection of technology, people, and process. You will bring clarity, structure, and momentum to real-world AI projects, aligning customer expectations with delivery outcomes and driving exceptional results for both customers and our business.\n\nThis is a hands-on, customer-facing role that is perfect for someone who enjoys taking ownership, generating real value for customers, and adapting fast in a rapidly evolving AI landscape.\n\nThe ideal candidate will come from a Consulting or Professional Services background, with experience in delivering AI, Data or SaaS solutions directly for enterprise customers.\n\nThe Role:\n\nYou will own the end-to-end delivery of multiple concurrent AI projects, acting as the primary delivery contact for customers and internal stakeholders throughout the project lifecycle.\n\nYou will:\n\n● Define scope, agree delivery plans, and set clear success criteria with customers and internal teams before work begins.\n\n● Own delivery through to completion, managing progress, dependencies, risks, issues, and change control across defined phases and sprint-based execution.\n\n● Lead all delivery communication, setting expectations, maintaining alignment, and escalating when required.\n\n● Build strong, trusted relationships with customers and internal stakeholders that support successful delivery.\n\n● This is a hands-on, customer-facing role that requires a high degree of ownership, energy, and a strong focus on delivering value.\n\nWhat you'll do at UiPath\n● Own end-to-end delivery of customer onboarding projects, acting as the primary contact for customers and internal stakeholders.\n\n● Define and agree scope, delivery plans, milestones, and success criteria upfront with customers and internal teams.\n\n● Build and maintain delivery plans, tracking progress, dependencies, resourcing, and milestones.\n\n● Maintain accurate reporting across RAG status, risks, issues, and change requests.\n\n● Lead regular delivery meetings, proactively managing risks and dependencies and escalating when timelines or resourcing are impacted.\n\n● Control scope through a structured change management process, ensuring impacts and trade-offs are clearly understood.\n\n● Contribute to improving delivery standards and ways of working, including use of Generative AI tools to optimise workflows.\n\nWhat you'll bring to the team\n\n● Proven customer-facing Project or Delivery Manager experience in a consultancy or technology environment.\n\n● Track record managing multiple complex projects concurrently in a fast-paced environment.\n\n● Strong scope management, including upfront definition, change control, and setting clear customer expectations.\n\n● Experience producing delivery documentation and managing formal sign-off.\n\n● Able to communicate scope and delivery changes in terms of customer and commercial impact.\n\nDesirable\n\n● Experience delivering AI, Data, or Analytics projects.\n\n● Domain experience in Retail, Manufacturing, or Supply Chain.\n\n● Change Management experience, particularly landing AI solutions into existing operations.\n\n● Jira and Confluence experience.\n\n● Experience working with or managing third parties during delivery.\n\nYou will thrive in this role if you:\n\n● Enjoy running multiple projects at once and instinctively know how to prioritise on-the-go\n\n● Are confident communicating when scope, timelines, or expectations need adjusting\n\n● Are curious about how AI can change how people work and make decisions, actively using AI tools to improve your own productivity and workflows\n\n● Collaborate well with diverse teams across engineering, product, sales and customer stakeholders\n\nWhy Join Us\n\n● Work at the forefront of Enterprise AI adoption.\n\n● Deliver solutions that transform how companies make decisions.\n\n● Collaborate with world-class teams across Data Science, Engineering, and Product Management\n\nMaybe you don’t tick all the boxes above—but still think you’d be great for the job? Go ahead, apply anyway. Please. Because we know that experience comes in all shapes and sizes—and passion can’t be learned.\n\nMany of our roles allow for flexibility in when and where work gets done. Depending on the needs of the business and the role, the number of hybrid, office-based, and remote workers will vary from team to team. Applications are assessed on a rolling basis and there is no fixed deadline for this requisition. The application window may change depending on the volume of applications received or may close immediately if a qualified candidate is selected.\n\nWe value a range of diverse backgrounds, experiences and ideas. We pride ourselves on our diversity and inclusive workplace that provides equal opportunities to all persons regardless of age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, and expression, national origin, disability, neurodiversity, military and/or veteran status, or any other protected classes. Additionally, UiPath provides reasonable accommodations for candidates on request and respects applicants' privacy rights. To review these and other legal disclosures, visit our privacy policy https://www.uipath.com/legal/trust-and-security/privacy-policy.",
